00:13:41.684 --> 00:13:45.584
So when we know something is effective, after that stage is usually when

227
00:13:45.824 --> 00:13:47.644
D&amp;I comes into most use.

228
00:13:48.544 --> 00:13:52.174
It's making that program work and ensuring that all

229
00:13:52.184 --> 00:13:56.144
populations are receiving what we know is effective and efficacious over time.

230
00:13:57.884 --> 00:14:01.704
This is a heuristic tool. It's looked like a subway map, which

231
00:14:01.764 --> 00:14:03.964
essentially helps us understand in what

232
00:14:05.884 --> 00:14:08.404
part of the journey of a practice of interest we're in.

233
00:14:08.464 --> 00:14:12.224
This is a common heuristic tool you'll see a lot used in implementation science

234
00:14:12.564 --> 00:14:16.164
to help us understand together as a group, for example, if the

235
00:14:16.224 --> 00:14:19.984
POI is at the stage that it needs to be in order to be considered

236
00:14:20.024 --> 00:14:23.704
implementation. So you start off with the identifying the

