687
00:40:53.500 --> 00:40:55.600
However, a precision

688
00:40:56.400 --> 00:40:59.120
prevention approach is not something

689
00:40:59.140 --> 00:41:02.870
that these systems have to do. So they

690
00:41:02.900 --> 00:41:06.100
wanted some guidance on what are the metrics that matter here.

691
00:41:06.660 --> 00:41:10.190
And then organize clinical implementation meetings to support the

692
00:41:10.280 --> 00:41:10.660
effort.

693
00:41:11.620 --> 00:41:15.500
So the implementation planning group came up with these strategies, and then

694
00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:19.520
we conducted key implementation interview actors, which is just

695
00:41:19.580 --> 00:41:23.440
a lot of jargony words for these are people who we would want to do these change

696
00:41:23.560 --> 00:41:27.460
things. We wanted to talk to the people whose roles would be affected from

697
00:41:27.520 --> 00:41:30.300
that mapping strategy of who we needed to do what.

698
00:41:30.890 --> 00:41:34.580
And from those interviews, we really dug in on, does your system have the capacity

699
00:41:34.620 --> 00:41:38.460
to be able to look at whether or not patients with diabetes are

700
00:41:38.500 --> 00:41:41.880
being screened at a better rate or not? Would that be hard for you?

701
00:41:41.900 --> 00:41:43.140
What kind of support would you need?

702
00:41:46.340 --> 00:41:50.010
The culmination of this work was the

703
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:53.860
development of an implementation toolkit, which would take me 20 minutes to go

704
00:41:53.940 --> 00:41:56.040
through in and of itself.

705
00:41:57.520 --> 00:42:01.480
And then the next phase was to determine the preliminary effectiveness of

706
00:42:01.520 --> 00:42:05.120
the implementation strategies for targeting colorectal cancer screening.

707
00:42:05.150 --> 00:42:07.120
And our primary outcomes were clinic-level

708
00:42:08.960 --> 00:42:12.440
screening uptake by test type and with an exploratory

709
00:42:12.600 --> 00:42:16.060
aim of colorectal cancer screening uptake by

710
00:42:16.100 --> 00:42:17.360
glycemic control.

711
00:42:18.480 --> 00:42:20.680
And then the key implementation outcomes were,

712
00:42:21.580 --> 00:42:24.720
is this implementation or implementation strategies, are they

713
00:42:24.840 --> 00:42:28.720
feasible? And are they acceptable by both the patients

714
00:42:28.900 --> 00:42:29.100
and the

715
00:42:30.040 --> 00:42:33.760
actors whose roles or functions changed as a result of

716
00:42:33.800 --> 00:42:37.756
them?So, this is just an example from the

717
00:42:38.136 --> 00:42:41.936
toolkit. We had multiple different educational pieces

718
00:42:43.376 --> 00:42:47.136
as a part of this. We wanted the practices to have all of the

719
00:42:47.176 --> 00:42:50.856
materials for the entire screening trajectory.

720
00:42:50.916 --> 00:42:54.506
So, a reminder that they needed screening, a result letter,

721
00:42:55.276 --> 00:42:56.036
a sample letter,

722
00:42:57.176 --> 00:43:00.916
infographics that could be printed about the elevated

723
00:43:00.996 --> 00:43:04.956
risk for colorectal cancer among patients with diabetes, and then

724
00:43:05.016 --> 00:43:07.916
general resources like the community guide one-pager.

725
00:43:08.996 --> 00:43:10.236
These were some of the metrics

726
00:43:11.036 --> 00:43:14.996
that we suggested people look

727
00:43:15.076 --> 00:43:19.016
at. So the number of patients overall who are eligible for colorectal cancer

728
00:43:19.096 --> 00:43:22.716
screening, the number of patients with diabetes who are eligible,

729
00:43:23.416 --> 00:43:24.416
the type of tests

730
00:43:25.876 --> 00:43:29.816
that people are being recommended to complete, which was generally

731
00:43:29.876 --> 00:43:30.696
stool-based tests.

732
00:43:31.556 --> 00:43:35.236
Most of the sites picked Cologuard because it's a three-year screening

733
00:43:35.336 --> 00:43:38.436
interval instead of a one-year screening interval with the

734
00:43:39.416 --> 00:43:43.156
rationale that if these could be reimbursed, it actually would

